the tests accordingly.

commit.message:
Bump to v9

Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>

Warn about upcoming expiration earlier

When using a spec that considers non-renewed key fatal, include
additional expiration warning before the fatal issue.  With GLEP63 v2,
the fatal period is 2 weeks, so warning period is 4 weeks.

Closes: https://github.com/mgorny/glep63-check/issues/4
Remove stale test keyring

Bump to v8

Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>

Update tests for GLEP63 v2.1

Add encryption subkey to all test keyrings (which implied generating
entirely new keys), and add extra tests for missing encryption subkey.

Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>

Fix accepting cv25519 (encryption) keys

Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>

Support GLEP63 v2.1: requiring encryption subkey

Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>

Bump to v7

Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>

Stop testing py34

Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>

Reduce expire:short to warning if key is being replaced

If there is at least one good replacement key, do not report
expire:short as fatal error.  This usually indicates that
the replacement is underway.  In the worst case, GnuPG will
automatically switch to the other key once the one in question expires.

Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>
